{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Amend how absences from the UK are calculated for the purpose of settled status",
        "additional_details": "The Government must review this rule and ensure absences are calculated in line with EU guidance, so that people do not lose out on rights to settled status.",
        "background": "In order to qualify for settled status persons with Pre-settled status cannot be absent from the country for more than six months in any 12-month period. This calculation should be based on fixed 12-month periods, starting with when the EU citizen arrived in the UK, not a rolling 12-month period.",
